documentation.text:
@notice Implements delegation of calls to other contracts, with proper
 forwarding of return values and bubbling of failures.
 It defines a fallback function that delegates all calls to the address
 returned by the abstract _implementation() internal function.
 @dev Forked from https://github.com/zeppelinos/zos-lib/blob/8a16ef3ad17ec7430e3a9d2b5e3f39b8204f8c8d/contracts/upgradeability/Proxy.sol
 Modifications:
 1. Reformat and conform to Solidity 0.6 syntax (5/13/20)

@dev Fallback function.
 Implemented entirely in `_fallback`.
@return The Address of the implementation.

@dev fallback implementation.
 Extracted to enable manual triggering.

@notice This contract implements a proxy that allows to change the
 implementation address to which it will delegate.
 Such a change is called an implementation upgrade.
 @dev Forked from https://github.com/zeppelinos/zos-lib/blob/8a16ef3ad17ec7430e3a9d2b5e3f39b8204f8c8d/contracts/upgradeability/UpgradeabilityProxy.sol
 Modifications:
 1. Reformat, conform to Solidity 0.6 syntax, and add error messages (5/13/20)
 2. Use Address utility library from the latest OpenZeppelin (5/13/20)

@dev Emitted when the implementation is upgraded.
 @param implementation Address of the new implementation.

@dev Returns the current implementation.
 @return impl Address of the current implementation
@return The address of the proxy admin.
@return The address of the implementation.

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Cannot change the admin of a proxy to the zero address"

arguments.value: Cannot change the admin of a proxy to the zero address

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Cannot change the admin of a proxy to the zero address"

documentation.text: @return adm The admin slot.

@dev Sets the address of the proxy admin.
 @param newAdmin Address of the new proxy admin.

typeDescriptions.typeString: literal_string "Cannot call fallback function from the proxy admin"

arguments.value: Cannot call fallback function from the proxy admin

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Cannot call fallback function from the proxy admin"

documentation.text: @dev Only fall back when the sender is not the admin.

@title FiatTokenProxy
 @dev This contract proxies FiatToken calls and enables FiatToken upgrades
